00:17:42.990 --> 00:17:46.060
to also consider the Ghetto.

00:17:46.060 --> 00:17:48.190
So the history of the
Jews of Venice,

00:17:48.190 --> 00:17:51.370
as we look at their cultural,
their intellectual achievements,

00:17:51.370 --> 00:17:54.870
the community that they
built based upon Jewish law,

00:17:54.870 --> 00:17:59.140
the fact that they had virtually de
facto autonomy within the Ghetto,

00:17:59.140 --> 00:18:03.050
et cetera -- for all of
the history of the Jews

00:18:03.050 --> 00:18:06.440
of Venice the word
Ghetto is lurking in there

00:18:06.440 --> 00:18:10.810
and survives down to the present.

00:18:10.810 --> 00:18:15.650
So if we begin to investigate
the institution of the Ghetto,

00:18:15.650 --> 00:18:21.730
the previous literature -- and
we're back now in the 1970s --

00:18:21.730 --> 00:18:25.420
there seemed to be
a general consensus

00:18:25.420 --> 00:18:31.620
that the word Ghetto first appeared
in Venice, but no consensus,

00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:34.240
really, about its entomology.

00:18:34.240 --> 00:18:40.230
Some saw its origin in a Venetian,
or at least Italian, source.

00:18:40.230 --> 00:18:45.640
And others derived it more
fancifully from Jewish sources.

00:18:45.640 --> 00:18:50.420
For example, the word ghetto -- the
word get meaning a bill of divorce

00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:54.170
because the Jews were segregated
from society, et cetera.

00:18:54.170 --> 00:19:01.370 position:56%
And over the centuries, much ink
had been spilled tracing the history

00:19:01.370 --> 00:19:06.020
of the word Ghetto, the
background before the Jews came

00:19:06.020 --> 00:19:08.880
in to be confined to one.

00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:13.350
Now, actually, the original meaning
of the word Ghetto was buried

00:19:13.350 --> 00:19:15.580
in the writings of certain 17th

00:19:15.580 --> 00:19:19.220
and 18th century Venetian
antiquarians and historians.

00:19:19.220 --> 00:19:23.110
And today it's been established
beyond any shadow of doubt

00:19:23.110 --> 00:19:27.860
that the word originated, as we
already heard today, in Venice,

00:19:27.860 --> 00:19:31.490
in a copper foundry in Venice.

00:19:31.490 --> 00:19:35.870
So, originally then, we have a
place called Il Ghetto, the ghetto,

00:19:35.870 --> 00:19:40.910
that had been the site of the
Municipal Copper Foundry of Venice.

00:19:40.910 --> 00:19:44.870
The main activity there had been
the production of bars of copper

00:19:44.870 --> 00:19:49.360
and also the alloy of bronze
used to make cannonballs.

00:19:49.360 --> 00:19:54.910 position:56%
Il Ghetto, from the Italian root
[foreign word], to throw or to cast,

00:19:54.910 --> 00:19:58.690
which we find surviving
today in English in words

00:19:58.690 --> 00:20:03.660
such as eject, jet, trajectory.

00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:07.180
Now, if you have a foundry you're
going to have waste products.

00:20:07.180 --> 00:20:09.940
And waste products have
to be dumped somewhere.

00:20:09.940 --> 00:20:17.470 position:56%
So across from the ghetto, Il
Ghetto, was a sort of swampy island.

00:20:17.470 --> 00:20:19.160
Remember, Venice was all --

00:20:19.160 --> 00:20:23.290
much of Venice was swampland
that was gradually drained

00:20:23.290 --> 00:20:29.330
and the piles were put down
and the city built on those --

00:20:29.330 --> 00:20:32.670
the land claimed from swamp.

00:20:32.670 --> 00:20:40.550
So, basically, the waste products
began being dumped on the island

00:20:40.550 --> 00:20:48.080
across from the ghetto and what
happened was that that island

00:20:48.080 --> 00:20:49.840
where things were dumped was --

00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:53.420
became known as Ghetto Nuovo
because it was the new ghetto,

00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:55.120
the expansion of the ghetto.

00:20:55.120 --> 00:20:59.460
Whereas the old area that had
been the foundry area became known

00:20:59.460 --> 00:21:01.700
as the Ghetto Vecchio.

00:21:01.700 --> 00:21:06.160
So we have two areas functioning
in Venice called Ghetto.

00:21:06.160 --> 00:21:09.740
One is the Ghetto Vecchio,
the original one.

00:21:09.740 --> 00:21:11.470
Those of you who have been there --

00:21:11.470 --> 00:21:14.150
I assume many of you
have been there, right?

00:21:14.150 --> 00:21:15.450
Fast show of hands.

00:21:15.450 --> 00:21:16.750
How are we doing?

00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:20.010
Okay. So, remember, the Ghetto
Vecchio is on the mainland --

00:21:20.010 --> 00:21:21.500
well, not on the mainland.

00:21:21.500 --> 00:21:24.250
Mainland terra firma means,
you know, back in [inaudible].

00:21:24.250 --> 00:21:27.400
It was on a very long island.

00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:32.930
You can go across on the main
streets there from one river,

00:21:32.930 --> 00:21:35.700
one canal, to the main
canal of Cannareggio.

00:21:35.700 --> 00:21:40.190
And the new area on which
things were being dumped is the

00:21:40.190 --> 00:21:42.870
Ghetto Nuovo.

00:21:42.870 --> 00:21:50.110 position:56%
Now, as the foundry of the
commune, which was producing cannons

00:21:50.110 --> 00:21:55.200
and balls and the like, as in the
15th century, Venice was embarked

00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:58.500
on expansion on the
mainland, terra firma.

00:21:58.500 --> 00:22:00.490
That means, literally,
the main land .

00:22:00.490 --> 00:22:04.170
Eventually reaching the
borders of Milan in the West.

00:22:04.170 --> 00:22:07.580
Lombardi, Milan, whatever
you want to call it.

00:22:07.580 --> 00:22:13.120
The ghetto could not produce enough
artillery and other things needed

00:22:13.120 --> 00:22:19.780
for the army and, therefore,
the manufacturer of the bronze,

00:22:19.780 --> 00:22:26.030 position:56%
the cannon balls, et cetera, was
moved to the arsenal and the island,

00:22:26.030 --> 00:22:29.080
the main land part, the island --

00:22:29.080 --> 00:22:34.150
I'm sorry, the Ghetto Vecchio
on the main larger island

00:22:34.150 --> 00:22:40.360
and the adjacent island of
the Ghetto Nuovo were sold off

00:22:40.360 --> 00:22:43.650
and they became areas

00:22:43.650 --> 00:22:48.140
which contained modest
two-story dwellings.

00:22:48.140 --> 00:22:51.410
And we'll skip the details that
have all been reconstructed,

00:22:51.410 --> 00:22:55.890
how they were divided up and
who owned them and the nature

00:22:55.890 --> 00:22:57.190
of the housing, et cetera.

00:22:57.190 --> 00:23:07.470
Now, as of then -- as of the
earlier days, and down to 1516

00:23:07.470 --> 00:23:11.100
as the Ambassador, I
think it was, pointed out,

00:23:11.100 --> 00:23:16.290
we have no Jews whatsoever
associated with the ghetto.

00:23:16.290 --> 00:23:21.170
It's low and middle income,
probably more lower income housing,

00:23:21.170 --> 00:23:24.150
mainly two stories, et cetera.

00:23:24.150 --> 00:23:28.740
Now, the interesting thing is,
as I began reading on the Ghetto

00:23:28.740 --> 00:23:34.800
and more important Jewish quarters
prior to this point of 1516

00:23:34.800 --> 00:23:39.130
in the Middle Ages,
there was a major problem

00:23:39.130 --> 00:23:42.840
in that the word ghetto was
frequently used to refer

00:23:42.840 --> 00:23:47.190
to Jewish quarters prior
to 1516 which, obviously,

00:23:47.190 --> 00:23:53.350
was a major anachronism, since
the word was not known outside

00:23:53.350 --> 00:23:54.720
of Venice.

00:23:54.720 --> 00:23:59.680
And, moreover, nobody would have
associated it in any way, shape,

00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:03.520
form, and manner with the Jews.

00:24:03.520 --> 00:24:11.270
Now, moreover, this word ghetto
was used by our contemporary,

00:24:11.270 --> 00:24:17.420
our contemporaneous
historians to refer

00:24:17.420 --> 00:24:22.440
to all types of Jewish quarters.

00:24:22.440 --> 00:24:25.680
Sometimes Jews are living
in a segregated area.

00:24:25.680 --> 00:24:31.690
Sometimes Jews are living
mixed among Christians.

00:24:31.690 --> 00:24:35.360
Sometimes Christians are living
in the supposed Jewish area.

00:24:35.360 --> 00:24:39.780
As an independent variable
sometimes walls were erected,

00:24:39.780 --> 00:24:42.160
sometimes they had gates.

00:24:42.160 --> 00:24:45.930
Because, remember, those
turbulent days, for security,

00:24:45.930 --> 00:24:49.970
areas were walled up, gates would
be locked at night, et cetera.

00:24:49.970 --> 00:24:52.090
The main thing is that
almost always,

00:24:52.090 --> 00:24:59.060
for all of these so-called Jewish
quarters, there was no reference

00:24:59.060 --> 00:25:02.660
to any legislation or
edict establishing them.

00:25:02.660 --> 00:25:06.370
And their origins, as a rule
-- there are a few exceptions,

00:25:06.370 --> 00:25:11.290
and if you're aware of one of those
few exceptions, just delete it.

00:25:11.290 --> 00:25:14.910
As a rule -- I'll deal
with one exception shortly.

00:25:14.910 --> 00:25:18.530
As a rule, the origins of
when the Jews were settled

00:25:18.530 --> 00:25:22.690
where they were are lost forever
in the mists of antiquity.

00:25:22.690 --> 00:25:25.960
I should say lost forever
because we all know that thanks

00:25:25.960 --> 00:25:29.970
to wonderful places like the Law
Library and Library of Congress

00:25:29.970 --> 00:25:34.010
and preservation of books, we'll
never know what will be discovered

00:25:34.010 --> 00:25:36.470
in terms of manuscripts
and books, et cetera.

00:25:36.470 --> 00:25:40.140 position:56%
But as of today, things are unclear.

00:25:40.140 --> 00:25:43.800
So if we go back to the --

00:25:43.800 --> 00:25:49.830
to Venice, if we read carefully
that edict of 1516, we will see --

00:25:49.830 --> 00:25:54.320
actually, legislation of the
Senate to 1516 proclaimed

00:25:54.320 --> 00:26:00.690 position:56%
by the Doge establishing the ghetto
and the subsequent course of events,

00:26:00.690 --> 00:26:05.990
we can conclude that the early
modern Venetian Ghetto was

00:26:05.990 --> 00:26:11.340
characterized by three important
necessary characteristics.

00:26:11.340 --> 00:26:13.860
First of all, it was compulsory.

00:26:13.860 --> 00:26:18.150
Every Jew had to live
inside the Ghetto.

00:26:18.150 --> 00:26:19.800
No exceptions.

00:26:19.800 --> 00:26:22.760
Number two, segregated.

00:26:22.760 --> 00:26:25.630
No Christians were
allowed to live inside it.

00:26:25.630 --> 00:26:27.250
In fact, the Christians
had to move out

00:26:27.250 --> 00:26:30.500
and the landlords were
granted a one-third increase

00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:32.870
to be free from all taxes.

00:26:32.870 --> 00:26:34.170
Very important.

00:26:34.170 --> 00:26:37.650
I meant it was worth much more
than a third more in order

00:26:37.650 --> 00:26:41.830
to get their tenants to move
out and the Jews could --

00:26:41.830 --> 00:26:44.230
the Jews had to pay more.

00:26:44.230 --> 00:26:46.970
Thirdly, the area was enclosed.

00:26:46.970 --> 00:26:52.400 position:56%
In other words, it was surrounded by
walls and a gate or gates that had

00:26:52.400 --> 00:26:57.540
to be locked at night and remained
so locked until the morning.

00:26:57.540 --> 00:27:02.270
So this then is the main
feature or features, if you wish,

00:27:02.270 --> 00:27:07.450
of a ghetto -- compulsory,
segregated, enclosed.

00:27:07.450 --> 00:27:10.720
Now during the counter-reformation
period

00:27:10.720 --> 00:27:15.650
that usually is taken
that dates from 1555.

00:27:15.650 --> 00:27:18.260
We'll stay out of the
problems of dating things.

00:27:18.260 --> 00:27:23.000
Gradually compulsory
segregated and enclosed areas

00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:29.670 position:56%
of Jewish residents were established
in all the other Italian cities,

00:27:29.670 --> 00:27:38.300
major cities with the exception of
Livorno, such as Rome, Florence,

00:27:38.300 --> 00:27:41.440
Sienna, Padua, Verona, Mantwin
[assumed spelling], elsewhere.

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:45.450
Italian Jews are living
behind ghetto walls.

00:27:45.450 --> 00:27:48.090 position:56%
Based on the Venetian experience all

00:27:48.090 --> 00:27:53.440
of these places were called ghettos
or, better in Italian, getti.

00:27:53.440 --> 00:27:55.440
And, therefore, I'm proposing

00:27:55.440 --> 00:27:58.100
that to the turrim [assumed
spelling] compulsory, segregated,

00:27:58.100 --> 00:28:00.800
enclosed, be accepted
as a definition

00:28:00.800 --> 00:28:04.340
of what an early modern
ghetto, Jewish ghetto,

00:28:04.340 --> 00:28:07.910
Italian Jewish ghetto,
was to differentiate it

00:28:07.910 --> 00:28:13.470
from subsequent quarters
often referred to as ghettos.

00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:19.200
Now, with this definition of what
constitutes the original ghetto

00:28:19.200 --> 00:28:21.930
in early modern Europe,
it should be noted

00:28:21.930 --> 00:28:27.360
that the were a few
compulsory segregated

00:28:27.360 --> 00:28:33.490
and enclosed Jewish quarters
in Europe before 1516,

00:28:33.490 --> 00:28:35.580
primarily in Castile and Aragon.

00:28:35.580 --> 00:28:37.250
Let me not talk more about that

00:28:37.250 --> 00:28:40.370
because it will take up
too much of our time.

00:28:40.370 --> 00:28:47.310
And most famously, of course,
was the Ghetto of Germanic Lands,

00:28:47.310 --> 00:28:50.770
Imperial Center, Frankfort,
where the Ghetto of Frankfort,

00:28:50.770 --> 00:28:55.520
established in 1464, would qualify

00:28:55.520 --> 00:28:59.150
as a ghetto before
the word so to speak.

00:28:59.150 --> 00:29:06.100
But these quarters were
never called ghettos.

00:29:06.100 --> 00:29:13.560 position:56%
They were only became called ghettos
after the end of the Venetian Ghetto

00:29:13.560 --> 00:29:15.940
with the coming of
the emancipation --

00:29:15.940 --> 00:29:22.560
that means the end of the 18th
century, the end of the 1700s.

00:29:22.560 --> 00:29:25.460
The word ghetto began to spread.

00:29:25.460 --> 00:29:30.190
And, for example, the segregated
compulsory enclosed Jewish quarter,

00:29:30.190 --> 00:29:34.680
Frankfort, was always called the
Judengasse, the Jewish Suite.

00:29:34.680 --> 00:29:38.840
Never called the ghetto
until after 1800.

00:29:38.840 --> 00:29:43.230 position:56%
The word began travelling northward.

00:29:43.230 --> 00:29:48.140
So, therefore, in the very
felicitous formulation

00:29:48.140 --> 00:29:53.600
of Robert von Pfiel, the city
of Venice retains the copyright

00:29:53.600 --> 00:29:59.450
for the semantically innovative
term ghetto as defining the locus

00:29:59.450 --> 00:30:02.840
of the settlement of
the Jews in the city.

00:30:02.840 --> 00:30:06.380
So every Italian city,
with the one exception

00:30:06.380 --> 00:30:08.890
as we said, Livorno, had a ghetto.

00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:12.650
And I do not mention more about
Livorno today because you have one

00:30:12.650 --> 00:30:16.810
of the world's leading experts on
the field sitting in the audience,

00:30:16.810 --> 00:30:20.630
Bernie Cooperman, who is at
the University of Maryland.

00:30:20.630 --> 00:30:23.480
An old friend from way, way back.

00:30:23.480 --> 00:30:27.950
Now, one of the new
insights on the ghetto,

00:30:27.950 --> 00:30:32.230
and this is something implied but
never quite absolutely realized,

00:30:32.230 --> 00:30:40.680
is that no matter how many gates
and what hour they were locked at,

00:30:40.680 --> 00:30:43.370
the ghetto was not
hermetically sealed,

00:30:43.370 --> 00:30:46.640
and it was very, very porous.

00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:49.380
And this has got to be
understood as the background

00:30:49.380 --> 00:30:52.560
for Venice as a melting pot.

00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:57.520
Not quite the melting pot as
a mixture of various peoples

00:30:57.520 --> 00:31:00.260
from various backgrounds.

00:31:00.260 --> 00:31:04.270
The ghetto was established, it
is true, to minimize contact

00:31:04.270 --> 00:31:06.320
between Christians and Jews.

00:31:06.320 --> 00:31:11.680
But the government only sought
to totally eliminate it at night

00:31:11.680 --> 00:31:15.760
because the Christian authorities
feared that under the cover

00:31:15.760 --> 00:31:19.810
of darkness all sorts of condemned

00:31:19.810 --> 00:31:24.670
and forbidden relations
could very easily occur.

00:31:24.670 --> 00:31:29.850
And their suspicion was
probably not without grounds.

00:31:29.850 --> 00:31:35.210
During the day not only could
Jews freely leave the ghetto,

00:31:35.210 --> 00:31:39.820
and Christians could enter at
will, but one group of Christians

00:31:39.820 --> 00:31:48.320
in Venice was even compelled to
come into the ghetto and here --

00:31:48.320 --> 00:31:51.580
this is most interesting
because from the very beginning,

00:31:51.580 --> 00:31:55.320
or let's say a few months
after the very beginning,

00:31:55.320 --> 00:32:00.320
the Venetian Government
insisted that the pawn shops,

00:32:00.320 --> 00:32:04.880
which were the reason for which
Jews were allowed into Venice,

00:32:04.880 --> 00:32:08.880
and which the government made
the Jews operate for the sake

00:32:08.880 --> 00:32:12.860 position:56%
of the urban poor, these pawn shops,

00:32:12.860 --> 00:32:16.020
the reason that the Jews
were tolerated in Venice was

00:32:16.020 --> 00:32:19.740
to be located in the ghetto.

00:32:19.740 --> 00:32:23.350
So that meant that any Christian
engaging in money lending,

00:32:23.350 --> 00:32:28.350
any Christian engaged in borrowing,
had twice to enter the ghetto.

00:32:28.350 --> 00:32:31.940
Once to pawn his object and we hope

00:32:31.940 --> 00:32:36.960
for his sake a second
time to redeem his pawn.

00:32:36.960 --> 00:32:41.500
Furthermore -- this is
often neglected -- the --

00:32:41.500 --> 00:32:46.460 position:56%
given the topography of Venice and
the size and location of the ghetto,

00:32:46.460 --> 00:32:51.420
it would be very inconvenient for
the Christian inhabitants of Venice

00:32:51.420 --> 00:32:54.860
to reach their destination on
occasion if they could not cut

00:32:54.860 --> 00:32:57.620
through the ghetto during the day.

00:32:57.620 --> 00:33:00.380
And I'll digress for a minute

00:33:00.380 --> 00:33:04.190
to show you how the most
unexpected sources dealing

00:33:04.190 --> 00:33:09.210 position:56%
with the most unexpected things draw
your attention to the commonplace.

00:33:09.210 --> 00:33:13.690
A proposal was made in the
-- I think it was 1764 --

00:33:13.690 --> 00:33:21.860
to establish a bullring in
the campo of the Ghetto Nuovo.

00:33:21.860 --> 00:33:24.870
Now, I've never personally
measured it, and I'm not quite sure

00:33:24.870 --> 00:33:26.650
if it's absolutely
correct because I can think

00:33:26.650 --> 00:33:28.620
of a couple of other large campos.

00:33:28.620 --> 00:33:31.120
But I remember reading
somewhere that the campo

00:33:31.120 --> 00:33:35.850 position:56%
of the Ghetto Nuevo was the second
largest, after San Marco, in Venice.

00:33:35.850 --> 00:33:38.890
Whether it is or isn't, the
point is it really is large

00:33:38.890 --> 00:33:41.190
and it is very convenient
for things.

00:33:41.190 --> 00:33:43.900
Now, there were some
objections to this proposal.

00:33:43.900 --> 00:33:49.090
And one of the objections was that
it would handicap the Christians

00:33:49.090 --> 00:33:52.560
who wanted to pass through
the ghetto on the days

00:33:52.560 --> 00:33:55.340
when it was closed
off for the bullring.

00:33:55.340 --> 00:33:57.770
The bullring never went up.

00:33:57.770 --> 00:34:02.170
There were no races
in the Ghetto Nuevo.

00:34:02.170 --> 00:34:06.570
It's been used for all sorts of
things since the emancipation time.

00:34:06.570 --> 00:34:08.310
Some of them -- I've never
personally been there

00:34:08.310 --> 00:34:10.720
on movie night, but I'm
sure it's very pleasant

00:34:10.720 --> 00:34:13.480
under a warm Venetian sky.

00:34:13.480 --> 00:34:14.780
So, anyways.

00:34:14.780 --> 00:34:20.260
The point is that Christians
were not strangers to the ghetto.

00:34:20.260 --> 00:34:24.220
And the converse of this is
agreement day Jews could be outside

00:34:24.220 --> 00:34:28.120
the ghetto freely and they could
associate with Christians and/

00:34:28.120 --> 00:34:32.200
or introduce all aspects
of Jewish culture,

00:34:32.200 --> 00:34:34.940
denuded of its Christian content --

00:34:34.940 --> 00:34:39.020
that's worth really a talk
in itself -- into the ghetto.

00:34:39.020 --> 00:34:43.600
Italian, or more accurately
Judeo-Venetian was the spoken

00:34:43.600 --> 00:34:45.330
language of the Jews.

00:34:45.330 --> 00:34:47.650
That's basically Venetian
dialect with a little Hebrew

00:34:47.650 --> 00:34:50.470
and Aramaic coming in
from the prayer book

00:34:50.470 --> 00:34:53.200
and the religious sources,
et cetera.

00:34:53.200 --> 00:34:56.290
And the Judeo-Venetian
was the everyday language.

00:34:56.290 --> 00:34:59.760
And the elite could
not only read Italian

00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:02.280
but they also could write it.

00:35:02.280 --> 00:35:05.860
So Jews are writing in
Italian, the vernacular.

00:35:05.860 --> 00:35:08.240
And even in Latin,
because in Latin --

00:35:08.240 --> 00:35:13.450
in Italy, Latin was not seen
as the language of the church,

00:35:13.450 --> 00:35:18.380 position:56%
but rather as a language of culture,
of the inhabitants of the republic

00:35:18.380 --> 00:35:19.900
of letters and, therefore,

00:35:19.900 --> 00:35:25.480
it was not considered
by the Jews to be taboo.

00:35:25.480 --> 00:35:31.600
So we always then have to remember
that the term ghetto refers only

00:35:31.600 --> 00:35:34.450
to the housing arrangements
of the Jews.

00:35:34.450 --> 00:35:38.190
And their culture was
determined by their environment,

00:35:38.190 --> 00:35:40.380
not by their housing arrangements.

00:35:40.380 --> 00:35:45.810
And the nature of the community was
further determined by the nature

00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:50.190
of the cosmopolitan city of Venice
which, as it was so well pointed

00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:54.650
out by the Ambassador, and again,
there's another long theme.

00:35:54.650 --> 00:36:00.660
You can discuss whether the laws
on the -- regarding the Jews were,

00:36:00.660 --> 00:36:04.510
quote, fair, humane,
et cetera, or not.

00:36:04.510 --> 00:36:09.970
By contemporary standards they
were certainly at least --

00:36:09.970 --> 00:36:13.620
they were certainly very
favorable to the Jews.

00:36:13.620 --> 00:36:15.600
But the key thing is that
everything was passed

00:36:15.600 --> 00:36:19.250 position:56%
by a council, by a legislative body.

00:36:19.250 --> 00:36:21.810
The Jews had every right of appeal

00:36:21.810 --> 00:36:25.330
and everything follows
the due process of law.

00:36:25.330 --> 00:36:28.760
The one thing that one can
learn from studying Venice's,

00:36:28.760 --> 00:36:32.110
that there were laws --
this is a lawful state

00:36:32.110 --> 00:36:36.860
and everything is proceeding
on a legal basis

00:36:36.860 --> 00:36:40.290
with committees sometimes one
feels maybe too many committees,

00:36:40.290 --> 00:36:41.590
but that's another issue.

00:36:41.590 --> 00:36:43.880
If you had a problem, you
established a committee.

00:36:43.880 --> 00:36:46.600
They already realized
that back then.

00:36:46.600 --> 00:36:49.200
And how often the committee
met, et cetera,

00:36:49.200 --> 00:36:51.060
and all that is another problem.

00:36:51.060 --> 00:36:55.070
But the point is this
is a law-abiding state.

00:36:55.070 --> 00:36:59.030
Now, looking ahead to the 19th and
20th century, because I really want

00:36:59.030 --> 00:37:03.760
to keep it moving, much
confusion arose as both past

00:37:03.760 --> 00:37:08.510
and contemporaneous dense
areas of Jewish residents

00:37:08.510 --> 00:37:12.220
that were neither compulsory
segregated nor enclosed came

00:37:12.220 --> 00:37:14.770
to be referred to as ghettos.

00:37:14.770 --> 00:37:18.510
It has been observed, in
fact, to the preliminary --

00:37:18.510 --> 00:37:22.540
we're talking now about the
end of the 20th century.

00:37:22.540 --> 00:37:23.960
It's certainly true today.

00:37:23.960 --> 00:37:27.840
Still true -- preliminary views
of ghetto definitions reveal

00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:30.700
that the ghetto was
probably the most misused

00:37:30.700 --> 00:37:36.590
and misunderstood spatial
concept used by social scientists.

00:37:36.590 --> 00:37:38.750
Clearly, the extended
use of the word ghetto,

00:37:38.750 --> 00:37:42.790
in many different senses,
created a blurring

00:37:42.790 --> 00:37:47.100
of the very important distinctions
between voluntary Jewish quarters

00:37:47.100 --> 00:37:50.020
and those that were
segregated and closed.

00:37:50.020 --> 00:37:54.060
These distinctions reflected
completely different attitudes

00:37:54.060 --> 00:37:58.640
toward Jews on the part of
governments and societies.

00:37:58.640 --> 00:38:03.220
Because of this blurring, modern
scholars have found it necessary

00:38:03.220 --> 00:38:06.790
to distinguish between
different types of ghettos.

00:38:06.790 --> 00:38:08.820
And I'll skip the details
on the terminology,

00:38:08.820 --> 00:38:12.880
but we have technical ghettos
and nontechnical ghettos.

00:38:12.880 --> 00:38:18.360
We have Louie Wirth, the great
sociologist of the Ghetto

00:38:18.360 --> 00:38:22.880
of the Chicago School, Colin
[inaudible] using the term

00:38:22.880 --> 00:38:25.590 position:56%
of voluntary ghetto which
certainly would have been considered

00:38:25.590 --> 00:38:29.990
oxymoronic by inhabitants
of the Italian Peninsula.

00:38:29.990 --> 00:38:34.950
And so it goes to distinguish
between forced ghettoization,

00:38:34.950 --> 00:38:38.050
self-ghettoization, et cetera.

00:38:38.050 --> 00:38:43.020 position:56%
Now, in this connection, we ought to
note that the 20th century ghettos

00:38:43.020 --> 00:38:48.060
of Nazi Europe, which is where
most people acquire their knowledge

00:38:48.060 --> 00:38:52.460
of what ghettos were, and as
Mitch Duneier demonstrated

00:38:52.460 --> 00:38:57.150
in a recent book, had much to do
with popularizing the word ghetto

00:38:57.150 --> 00:39:00.210
in the Afro-American world,
although it was known before that.

00:39:00.210 --> 00:39:04.160
But it -- your [inaudible]
soldiers in the American Army

00:39:04.160 --> 00:39:07.030
and Europe saw the Nazi ghettos.

00:39:07.030 --> 00:39:09.720
These ghettos of modern Europe,

00:39:09.720 --> 00:39:11.850
if the 20th century is
still considered modern,

00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:17.700 position:56%
differed fundamentally from those of
the early modern Italian Peninsula.

00:39:17.700 --> 00:39:25.040 position:56%
The Italian ghettos were supposed to
provide the Jews with a permanent,

00:39:25.040 --> 00:39:29.110
clearly-defined space in
Christian society in accordance

00:39:29.110 --> 00:39:35.340
with the traditional Christian
theology that the Jews were to live

00:39:35.340 --> 00:39:41.520
in a subjected condition until
the second coming of Jesus.

00:39:41.520 --> 00:39:45.700
This was to prove the rejection
of Christianity by God.

00:39:45.700 --> 00:39:51.090 position:56%
They're living under abject
circumstances until the Messiah came

00:39:51.090 --> 00:39:54.280
to redeem all of humanity,
et cetera.

00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:58.730
On the other hand, the Nazi
ghettos were very, very different

00:39:58.730 --> 00:40:03.050
because they in no way had
anything permanent about them.

00:40:03.050 --> 00:40:07.740
This was no way a permanent
settling of the Jewish problem

00:40:07.740 --> 00:40:12.600 position:56%
by providing them with a living area
because of their economic utility

00:40:12.600 --> 00:40:17.030
in Christian society, but
rather once the decision

00:40:17.030 --> 00:40:20.180
to embark upon the final
solution had been made,

00:40:20.180 --> 00:40:23.630
the ghettos constituted
a temporary waystation

00:40:23.630 --> 00:40:25.630
on the road to emancipation.

00:40:25.630 --> 00:40:29.200
And these two different kinds of
ghettos reflect the difference

00:40:29.200 --> 00:40:34.040
between traditional religious
anti-Judaism on the one hand

00:40:34.040 --> 00:40:39.660
and modern racial antisemitism
in its ultimate form.

00:40:39.660 --> 00:40:43.280
In the case of anti-Judaism
a Jew could escape the ghetto

00:40:43.280 --> 00:40:44.580
by conversion.

00:40:44.580 --> 00:40:46.350
There was a way out.

00:40:46.350 --> 00:40:51.750
While in the case of modern
antisemitism, one could not escape

00:40:51.750 --> 00:40:56.840
by one's own conversion nor by the
conversion of one's parents nor

00:40:56.840 --> 00:41:00.680
by the conversion of less
than three grandparents.

00:41:00.680 --> 00:41:03.780
So, interestingly the difference --

00:41:03.780 --> 00:41:09.910
different natures of a compulsory
segregated and closed ghettos

00:41:09.910 --> 00:41:15.360 position:56%
of pre-emancipation Christian
Europe on the one hand and those of,

00:41:15.360 --> 00:41:19.870
on the other hand, of Nazi-occupied
Europe, lead to the conclusion

00:41:19.870 --> 00:41:23.040
that the experience of
European Jewry from 1940

00:41:23.040 --> 00:41:28.180
to 1945 did not constitute
a return to the Middle Ages,

00:41:28.180 --> 00:41:30.850
but rather constituted the advent

00:41:30.850 --> 00:41:36.040
of a completely new
and far worse reality.

00:41:36.040 --> 00:41:39.100
Indeed, the statement or
the remis-statement better,

00:41:39.100 --> 00:41:41.300
that the Holocaust
represented a return

00:41:41.300 --> 00:41:46.010
to the Middle Ages is probably
one of the most misunderstood --

00:41:46.010 --> 00:41:52.210
one of the most widely spread
misunderstandings associated

00:41:52.210 --> 00:41:54.140
with the word ghetto.

00:41:54.140 --> 00:42:00.280
Now, to begin our descent to pick
up on Roberta's very apt analogy,

00:42:00.280 --> 00:42:06.580
I see a story and I'm very bothered
by the use of the word ghetto

00:42:06.580 --> 00:42:10.340
to describe a wide range of
Jewish quarters, let alone those

00:42:10.340 --> 00:42:15.120
of subsequent current
application to the situation

00:42:15.120 --> 00:42:18.970
of other minority groups,
whatever their nature.

00:42:18.970 --> 00:42:22.040
And I hope that, after
a few more minutes --

00:42:22.040 --> 00:42:26.100
I promise not more than a couple --
you, too, will share this concern.

00:42:26.100 --> 00:42:30.340
The basic problem is as
one historian put it,

00:42:30.340 --> 00:42:34.240
the word ghetto has lived
through more metamorphoses

00:42:34.240 --> 00:42:37.800
than any other word with
such a long history.

00:42:37.800 --> 00:42:41.420
So, when one hears the word
ghetto, one has to ask,

00:42:41.420 --> 00:42:46.570
to which ghetto is the speaker
or author intending to refer,

00:42:46.570 --> 00:42:50.780
and does the word invoke
the desired image?

00:42:50.780 --> 00:42:55.830
If the compulsory segregated
enclosed Jewish quarters of Venice,

00:42:55.830 --> 00:43:01.200
Rome, and Florence were ghettos,
if the Lower East Side of New York

00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:07.920
and Whitechapel and wherever else
were ghettos, if Warsaw, Lage,

00:43:07.920 --> 00:43:11.190
and Bialystok were
ghettos, if Westchester

00:43:11.190 --> 00:43:18.150
and Newton are golden ghettos, what
exactly does the word ghetto mean?

00:43:18.150 --> 00:43:20.840
Incidentally, ghettos
did not cease --

00:43:20.840 --> 00:43:24.860
did not exist in pre-World
War II Eastern Europe.

00:43:24.860 --> 00:43:27.100
The alleged ghettos
of Eastern Europe,

00:43:27.100 --> 00:43:31.120
which should be called [foreign
word] or [foreign word],

00:43:31.120 --> 00:43:37.430 position:56%
and even the entire pre-World War
II, pre-World War I, palo-settlement

00:43:37.430 --> 00:43:41.280
as a whole, cannot
accurately be called a ghetto

00:43:41.280 --> 00:43:46.200
in the early modern Italian sense
because some Jews were allowed

00:43:46.200 --> 00:43:48.390
to live inside it while --

00:43:48.390 --> 00:43:52.900
outside it, while Christians
could live within it.

00:43:52.900 --> 00:43:55.650
I haven't seen it for
many years, decades,

00:43:55.650 --> 00:43:57.210
but I believe that in <i>Fiddler</i>

00:43:57.210 --> 00:44:03.030
<i>on the Roof </i>you will
not see any ghettos.

00:44:03.030 --> 00:44:07.410
Now, if our understanding
of the word is unclear,

00:44:07.410 --> 00:44:11.660
how can our understanding
of the Jewish Experience be?

00:44:11.660 --> 00:44:16.550
And when we speak of
non-Jewish ghettos in the cities

00:44:16.550 --> 00:44:21.130 position:56%
of North America, South Africa, and
elsewhere, what are we referring to?

00:44:21.130 --> 00:44:24.560
Is it a compulsory area
established by the state

00:44:24.560 --> 00:44:27.820
or by zoning laws or by redlining?

00:44:27.820 --> 00:44:33.450 position:56%
If it is compulsory, is it enclosed,
is it gated, is there a curfew,

00:44:33.450 --> 00:44:38.480
is every person who is living in
that ghetto required to live in it

00:44:38.480 --> 00:44:41.730
and no members of any
other community are allowed

00:44:41.730 --> 00:44:44.350
to do in it -- live in it?

00:44:44.350 --> 00:44:48.150
What image comes to our mind
when we hear the word ghetto?

00:44:48.150 --> 00:44:53.500
We may or we will, probably,
encounter this important question

00:44:53.500 --> 00:44:58.380
when we read the morning newspaper
or watch the evening news.

00:44:58.380 --> 00:45:04.030
Now, clearly, the -- clearly,
the situation cannot be rectified

00:45:04.030 --> 00:45:07.160
by a global change in every case

00:45:07.160 --> 00:45:11.580
in which the word ghetto has
been used in print in the past.

00:45:11.580 --> 00:45:16.640
What we can do, however, is use the
word ghetto with some explanation,

00:45:16.640 --> 00:45:21.090
with some nuancing, and with a
full awareness of the problematics

00:45:21.090 --> 00:45:26.040
of identifying a ghetto and
share this awareness with others,

00:45:26.040 --> 00:45:29.760
that the word ghetto has
changed its meanings.

00:45:29.760 --> 00:45:35.360
Now, it's all right if a
word changes its meaning.

00:45:35.360 --> 00:45:41.780
But the problem is when the old
meanings are used simultaneously

00:45:41.780 --> 00:45:45.880
and you have a pile of meanings
and they're all being jumbled

00:45:45.880 --> 00:45:52.750
in together, and it's not clear
what the user is referring to.

00:45:52.750 --> 00:45:54.050
It's unclear.

00:45:54.050 --> 00:45:59.130
And our understanding of a
past also becomes very blurred.

00:45:59.130 --> 00:46:04.780
So I'm suggesting to conclude
the differentiated use

00:46:04.780 --> 00:46:09.700
of the word ghetto will lead
to a much better understanding

00:46:09.700 --> 00:46:13.180
of a major feature of
both Jewish history,

00:46:13.180 --> 00:46:15.470
of world history, and
-- I said both.

00:46:15.470 --> 00:46:17.960 position:56%
I should say all of -- never ad lib.

00:46:17.960 --> 00:46:23.420
Either write that out and stick
to it or ad lab completely.

00:46:23.420 --> 00:46:26.790
That will lead to a much better
understanding of a major feature

00:46:26.790 --> 00:46:28.860
of Jewish history, world
history, and urban history.

00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:35.540
If I may cite the titles of one of
my articles, that while originally,

00:46:35.540 --> 00:46:38.570
while every ghetto
was a Jewish quarter,

00:46:38.570 --> 00:46:43.160
not every Jewish quarter
was a ghetto.

