01:15:23.760 --> 01:15:26.980
There's no answer for that.

01:15:26.980 --> 01:15:30.560
Why did -- so, many -- the
question has entered into --

01:15:30.560 --> 01:15:33.180 position:56%
well, I already mentioned that --
has entered into a small controversy

01:15:33.180 --> 01:15:37.680
over who wrote <i>The
Merchant of Venice </i>.

01:15:37.680 --> 01:15:42.450
To the arguments noted above under
human rights, take for granted

01:15:42.450 --> 01:15:45.700
that Shylock is being treated
differently and unfairly,

01:15:45.700 --> 01:15:48.520
but do not describe in detail
the kinds of prohibitions

01:15:48.520 --> 01:15:50.520
under which he would
have lived and worked.

01:15:50.520 --> 01:15:53.190
So as Professor Ravid
mentioned, the ghetto was located

01:15:53.190 --> 01:15:56.620
in the northwest part of the
city on two small islands.

01:15:56.620 --> 01:16:00.030
The islands were linked to
the city by two small bridges,

01:16:00.030 --> 01:16:03.560
always under guard by Christian
soldiers who were paid,

01:16:03.560 --> 01:16:07.660
not by the city, but by the
inhabitants of the ghetto.

01:16:07.660 --> 01:16:11.360
Residents of the ghetto could not
leave between sundown and sunrise

01:16:11.360 --> 01:16:13.850 position:56%
because the city closed the bridges.

01:16:13.850 --> 01:16:16.340
Moreover, the other parts
of the ghetto were separated

01:16:16.340 --> 01:16:19.040
from the water by high walls.

01:16:19.040 --> 01:16:21.940
Finally, the Jews had to
pay the cost of two boats

01:16:21.940 --> 01:16:26.010
that kept the ghetto
surrounded and under guard.

01:16:26.010 --> 01:16:28.060
If the Jews left the
ghetto during the day,

01:16:28.060 --> 01:16:31.300
they had to wear identifying
marks, yellow badges

01:16:31.300 --> 01:16:34.800
or skullcaps during
their stay in the city.

01:16:34.800 --> 01:16:38.560
In addition to the requirement
to live in the ghetto and abide

01:16:38.560 --> 01:16:43.280
by its exclusions, Shylock and all
other Jews in Venice faced frequent

01:16:43.280 --> 01:16:46.630
and significant taxation
as well as a large number

01:16:46.630 --> 01:16:49.010
of government economic regulations.

01:16:49.010 --> 01:16:51.310
They could not engage
in numerous trades.

01:16:51.310 --> 01:16:54.310
They were prohibited from
engaging in numerous trades.

01:16:54.310 --> 01:16:57.900
And limited to particular
trades like pawn shops,

01:16:57.900 --> 01:17:00.970
second-hand clothes,
and money lending.

01:17:06.080 --> 01:17:08.180
The Catholic Church
prescribed some of the --

01:17:08.180 --> 01:17:09.950
proscribed some of this activity.

01:17:09.950 --> 01:17:14.210
So the Venetian economy needed
the participation of the Jews.

01:17:14.210 --> 01:17:15.510
That was the deal.

01:17:15.510 --> 01:17:17.390
The Jews could live in
Venice in the ghetto

01:17:17.390 --> 01:17:19.530
if they provided those services.

01:17:19.530 --> 01:17:22.040
So it should be obvious
at this point that there's

01:17:22.040 --> 01:17:25.890
at least one strong reason for
Shylock to insist throughout most

01:17:25.890 --> 01:17:28.830
of the trial scene on
repayment of his bond.

01:17:28.830 --> 01:17:32.950
This is an individual who has very
limited rights and the according

01:17:32.950 --> 01:17:36.910
of those rights to him are
all beyond his control.

01:17:36.910 --> 01:17:39.210
The city determines
what Shylock may do

01:17:39.210 --> 01:17:41.500 position:56%
and what he's prohibited from doing.

01:17:41.500 --> 01:17:45.190
From physical movement to
business occupation to the conduct

01:17:45.190 --> 01:17:48.350 position:56%
of commerce, Shylock is constrained.

01:17:48.350 --> 01:17:52.340
Here in <i>The Merchant of Venice </i>he
at last possesses a piece of paper,

01:17:52.340 --> 01:17:55.970
a contract, a bond, that
seems to give him some rights.

01:18:00.310 --> 01:18:04.210
Can he be blamed for
reading it with blinders,

01:18:04.210 --> 01:18:08.700
ignoring the larger context of
discrimination that Portia brings

01:18:08.700 --> 01:18:13.330 position:56%
so dramatically to bear when she
argues her case under the Alien Act?

01:18:13.330 --> 01:18:17.780
Should the court be so quick to
condemn the expressive nature

01:18:17.780 --> 01:18:22.090
of Shylock's small page of freedom?

01:18:22.090 --> 01:18:32.310
So, I'm arguing that Shylock has a
desire to express his own yearning

01:18:32.310 --> 01:18:37.890
for freedom through the
insistence on the bond.

01:18:37.890 --> 01:18:41.560
And now the symbolism
behind the penalty.

01:18:41.560 --> 01:18:44.140
Shylock argues that his
motive in signing the bond

01:18:44.140 --> 01:18:48.040
with Antonio was not to seek
the life of any citizen,

01:18:48.040 --> 01:18:51.050
even though the bond called
for the pound of flesh.

01:18:51.050 --> 01:18:54.620
Motive must be important -- so
this is under the Alien Act --

01:18:54.620 --> 01:18:57.350
motive must be important
because otherwise it's possible

01:18:57.350 --> 01:19:01.520
than an alien doctrine, including a
Jew who helped a Venetian citizen,

01:19:01.520 --> 01:19:03.560
could come under the law.

01:19:03.560 --> 01:19:06.770
Likewise, an alien who accidentally
causes a Venetian to fall

01:19:06.770 --> 01:19:09.850
and cut himself could be
prosecuted under the law.

01:19:09.850 --> 01:19:12.290
So motive is important.

01:19:12.290 --> 01:19:15.360
But there's a better,
more compelling argument

01:19:15.360 --> 01:19:18.420
that I don't think has been raised
anywhere else in the literature

01:19:18.420 --> 01:19:20.630
on <i>The Merchant of Venice </i>.

01:19:20.630 --> 01:19:24.270 position:56%
I would argue that the motive behind
the particular penalty demanded

01:19:24.270 --> 01:19:29.730 position:56%
by Shylock, the pound of flesh, is,
in fact, a proxy or a symbol of life

01:19:29.730 --> 01:19:34.100
in the ghetto, and more
incisively, of the ghetto itself.

01:19:34.100 --> 01:19:39.040
The ghetto is cut out of the body
of the city of Venice and exists

01:19:39.040 --> 01:19:41.240
within it, but separately.

01:19:41.240 --> 01:19:45.760
The pound of flesh, once removed,
interrupts the smooth functioning

01:19:45.760 --> 01:19:49.520
of the human body just as the
distinct physical separation

01:19:49.520 --> 01:19:54.790
of the ghetto interrupts the
continuity and the flow of Venice.

01:19:54.790 --> 01:19:58.000
So, Dr. Ravid was talking about
the need for Christians to be able

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:00.110 position:56%
to cross the ghetto, to come and go.

01:20:00.110 --> 01:20:03.040
The ghetto interrupts
that natural flow.

01:20:03.040 --> 01:20:06.860
Shylock is showing Antonio and the
rulers of Venice through his ruse

01:20:06.860 --> 01:20:11.330
of the pound of flesh just what the
ghetto's separate status is doing

01:20:11.330 --> 01:20:14.010
to Venice and to the
Jews who are forced

01:20:14.010 --> 01:20:17.570 position:56%
to live there in relative isolation.

01:20:17.570 --> 01:20:21.100
This possibility is supported
by two historical references.

01:20:21.100 --> 01:20:25.250
First in 1516 the decree
that created the ghetto

01:20:25.250 --> 01:20:28.980
